    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received February 2.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson reports that the insurgents have withdrawn their restrictive
                        orders, that ships of all nationalities are no longer kept from coming to
                        the shore, and notes a favorable progress of commerce, all of which he says
                        is due to the influence of the war vessels of the United States having
                        stopped the insurgents’ fire against American merchant vessels.</p>
            </div>
